	WOOOOOOW!!	I will make this one short and sweet :)Vegas is a magical city where you can do whatever your heart desires...as long as you have the cash! I am speaking of world class dining, over-the-top VIP treatment at clubs, high roller treatment at casinos, and uber luxurious spa treatments.On to the actual review of Planet HollywoodFIrst of all, the location is PRIME!! center strip. Located across from the bellagio and the new City center being constructed. If you plan to see the whole strip this would be a good place to stay, because its very near the middle of the strip, plus there is the Miracle Mile mall attached to it so you can shop for the essentials (alcohol, food, pharmacy stuff) rite downstairs without paying resort prices. We got a resort room with a view of the bellagio fountains and our pool area. No complains huge room, but the movie theme was a little weird, Baywatch, cool pics but not a baywatch fan. Also, the only real complain about the room was the position of the TV; it did not face the bed at all, you couldn't move it or the bed, you could only watch it from the chairs. Best part of the room was the washroom, HUGE, as big as a bedroom, not just his and her sinks, but his and her sides, separate sides for boys with their own toiletries and ladies sides with vanity and the works. In the middle huge open space, it has a giant soaker tub, standup shower with seat and of course a toilet with its own door.The atmosphere was rockstar-ish, everytime you went downstairs it was like a party was going on. Good place to get drinks and people watch, the pleasure pit is always fun and the prive the nite club was better than I thought it was going to be. The pool area can do with a little more PH style, it seems a little bland and almost family oriented, nice view of the paris tower though. To eat there is the earl of sandwich, good place to grab a bite, cheap. Tried spice market buffet, now my second fav buffet in Vegas, reasonably priced considering what you get.The overall impression is a good one, very hip and trendy, still has some work to do here and there, upgraded pool area is the most wanting. Service was friendly throughout the hotel, only had one issue with the maid, she wouldn't give me more towels than she thought I needed. Rooms are amazing, vibe is amazing, location is amazing, and dining is amazing!!!Planet Hollywood ROCKS!.p.s. Holly Madison just started headlining for Peepshow.....WooOoOoOOoOOOW!!	
	Planet Hollywood Las Vegas Review	huge rooms, great location as its in the middle of the strip and the buffet is amazing!!! the free bottle of whiskey and wine also helped!!	
	Highly Recommend perfect location on the Strip	We stayed here on the first part of a nine night trip to the States from 16 November. The hotel is located right on the middle of the strip making getting around so easy. On check in we didn't have to queue and the whole process took less that 5 mins. Our room was on 31st floor with a view of the strip and had two queen size beds, large bathroom and was spotlessly clean. The room also had a connecting door and when I asked if we could be moved to a room without one, we were upgraded to an even larger room with more luxurious bathroom for the inconvenience of moving. The whole complex is very big and can be a bit confusing finding your way around but everything soon clicks into place you find your bearings no problem. If I am ever lucky enough to return to Vegas I would stay at Planet Hollywood without hesitation.	
