Nov 13 2009 	Something for Everyone in Vegas	Planet Hollywood has something for almost everyone (with the exception of young children which is the case for all of Vegas in general). The location is centrally located with the new CityCenter and Bellagio across the street and Paris to the right. The Hard Rock Casino is just a short cab ride down Harmon as well. I stayed in one of the basic rooms but would describe them as fairly modern with framed hollywood memorabilia inside. The amenities and view of the strip were decent. Do be aware that there is a $5 (non-optional) per night resort charge that includes things like 2 bottles of water and a newspaper each day.The casino is nice with the crowd being described as around middle age. There are a number of shows including Peep Show and the Steve Wyrick magic show. One of the best features is the Miracle Mile Shops that is attached to the casino/hotel. PH offers quite a few brand name restaurants rather than the typical &quot;casino&quot; restaurants so it was quite easy to please the mainstream crowd. The Spice Market buffet was decent but then again, I'm not sure if any Vegas buffet has wowed me. Sammy Hagar's Cabo Wabo Cantina literally just opened in place of Trader Vics.As for suggestions, I would recommend that everyone join the A-List players club in the event you decide to spend most of the time gambling there. For those wishing to visit the new CityCenter resort, this may be one of the closest, lower-priced alternatives. Overall, would I stay at PH again................yes (especially since you earn points with the Starwood Preferred Guest program.	
