Nov 3 2009 	Fantastic hotel to stay at	I loved this hotel - from the minute I arrived to the minute I left! We stayed from Monday 26th October to Friday 30th october and loved everything about it!I shall give a list of everything I loved about this hotel.The hotel is in the very best spot in town - right at the heart of everything!The check-in queue was short (3 people in front) and one of they guys was so efficient that he checked in two of the people in front of us and then us in the same time that the others all checked in one person!! His name was EVAN!! The lobby was clean, bright and very attractive.The shop where you get the free bottles (full-size 750ml bottles always had at least 2 staff serving - whata great offer - the free booze!! We had champagne 2 nights of the stay and I saved a bottle of whiskey and gin to take home to England with me!!The lifts were easily accessed and there are 6 on both the north and south sides of the hotel - we were lucky - we were on the 12th floor and just around the corner from the lifts!The room was LOVELY!!! At night the room could have done with an overhead light rather than just the 3 lamps but it was ok and in the day it was ok anyway. But of course the massive bright bathroom was great for putting on your make-up!! I loved the size of the tub and the shower - big enough for two! Also the two sinks was great - we were just a couple but it would be great for a group of friends to get ready at the same time. Hubbie was in the loo and I was in the shower at the same time - how good is that at saving time!We had a non-smoking room so got two double beds which made the room larger and I loved the big hall into the room, with the bathroom off it so it felt like a suite rather than just a room. The maid had always been when we got back to the room anywhere between 2 and 4 in the afternoon and had always made the beds, cleaned the bathroom and put fresh water bottles in the cabinet. Our newspaper arrived every morning.We were in the Burt Reynolds room which sutied hubbie cos he loves him!!The best place to eat in the hotel (the only place we ate actually) was the Spice Buffet - I cannot recommend it highly enough - especially the Indian food!! As Indian food is now the Englishmans favourite meal, I know my spices and this was the BEST Indian food I have ever tasted!!! We got a 2 for the price of 1 ticket with our room cards so we used this, I am not sure if I would like to pay the full price for it though! I hate spending lots of money on food!The atmosphere of the hotel is lively, young and hip! I am in my 40's and hubbie is 50 but we still loved the hotel. It wasnt too busy and we had fun watching the gambling in all the parts of the casino. We didnt gamble too much but the tables give a good bit back so that you can play each table for ages on a relatively small bet!The girls on the tables are dressed in basques and tiny shorts and the dancers in the pleasure pit are sexy but I wouldnt say its any worse than you see on TV or walking down the street sometimes!!We are not into nighclubs so didnt use the hotel ones and cant comment. We didnt use the spa , swimming pools or gym either.On the day of going home, we left our cases in the baggage drop off room and they held our cases til 4.30pm so that we could spend the day doing what we wanted unencmbered with cases!! It is no trouble to them.We took a bus from the airport to the hotel ($6 each) and got a taxi back to the airport on going home ($15 - we gave the driver $20) but I would definately recommend the bus from the aiport to the hotel because the traffic getting to the hotel is heavier than getting back to the airport and would have cost a lot more to get from the airport to the hotel!! The taxis wait just outside the lobby and there is always a man there checking you in with a taxi so that you know you are not being ripped off.I would also say that going to the GRAND CANYON is a MUST!!! We used Heli-USA - we got the tickets from one of the booths (dont get it from the hotel it cost a fortune!) We got te trip that had a helicopter flight from McCarron Airport to the Grand Canyon, flying over the Hoover Dam, Lake Mead and Colorado River and flies THROUGH the Grand Canyon and stops for lunch at a cowboy ranch (dont expect too much here though!!).The other thing I would recommend is that you need to dress up a bit here - I didnt think you had to and felt a bit underdressed even in the daytime!!I think a week is needed here - we only had 4 nights, and we didnt do all we wanted to. Planet Hollywood is a great hotel - I would NOT recommend one of the cheaper hotels - they are not nice - and I would say that if you want top notch hotels then the Mandalay Bay, Bellagio and Wynn hotels are for you.If you want any further details please email me.All in all - this hotel is a great place to stay - I would recommend it to anyone!!	
