sn’t working the first night. We took this complaint to the desk downstairs who sent someone up immediately to change it, although they were rude on the phone when we first rang down. After kicking up a fuss at the desk, we finally got comped the spice market buffet for 4 which was actually very good. We also ate at Planet Dailies for lunch which was very good value. The Miracle Mile shops are quite hard to navigate, we kept getting lost. The casino has a great modern feel to it and is like no other on the strip. I wish we’d spent more time in the casino. I was addicted to the Ebay slot machine which paid out quite well! We also ate at Blondies in Miracle Mile which has Beer Pong on a Tuesday night, it’s like a local college beer night, I would recommend this!!! The pool is on the 7th floor (I Think?) and is very basic, literally just a rectangle and there was only 1 cocktail waitress the day I went. The spa in the resort is very good, it was very quiet when we went for our massages, mine was by a guy called Bernard who was very professional. We made use of the sauna and Jacuzzi which we had to ourselves. Would definitely stay here again.	
Oct 11 2009 	Lively clean and fun hotel in the perfect location.	Just got back from 5 nights stay at Planet Hollywood, Las Vegas. Was celebrating my 30th with some friends and had an amazing time. In brief this hotel is great!!We booked the hotel/flights with British Airways and by flying to LAX Los Angeles we were offered a huge discount. The flights were ok but as we didn't check in online, we ended up sitting separately. We then hired what can only be described as a massive truck from Alamo and drove to Las Vegas. Despite the horror stories I've heard about the drive it didn't take long and was quite enjoyable. We arrived at the Planet Hollywood at 7pm. The hotel provides free valet parking and the valet staff were friendly and helpful. We walked straight up to the well staffed check in desk and the guy who served us was helpful and friendly. He offered me a complementary upgraded room but wasn't able to upgrade all of us so I preferred a room close to my friends. He then gave us all vouchers for discounted shows and gambling. We were also given vouchers for free alcohol. Didn't expect much but got a big bottle of brand spirits or champagne every night!! When I did return to the lobby to collect my free booze I did notice that check in does get busy at random times. Guess we were lucky. We all had rooms on the 16th rooms. They were HIP rooms and each had 2 queen size beds, LCD TV, loads of space and great decor. They were dark but that really suited the contemporary style. The bathrooms had a bath and separate shower and to my girlfriends delight a separate toilet. The rooms were clean and the maid service provided 2 bottles of complementary water daily. VERY IMPORTANT SAFETY NOTE - The room doesn't lock unless the handles in the correct position when you close it . On 2 occasions in the night i heard someone trying the handle (on one occasion it might have been my drunk friend Justin Hurley). The hotel casino wasn't the biggest in Vegas but had a young crowd and energetic atmosphere. The drinks in the casino bars were $13 each so it was actually cheaper to spend a few dollars in the machines and take advantage of the complementary drinks offered by the cocktail waitresses. The restaurants in the hotel were really good. The buffet was $14 dollars for breakfast and $20 for lunch. We ate all over vegas but my favorite dinner was at the mexican restaurant in PH off the casino. Good points - Great location, centre of the exiting part of the strip. Young crowd and lively atmosphere. Good food, free drinks, efficient friendly helpful staff. Ice and vending machines on each floor.Bad points - I didn't win any money!! Nightclubs advertised as free but they tried to sting us for $30 each entry. When we declined they offered free entry for the girls and $20 dollars for the guys. Having being told it was free entry only 5 minutes earlier we decided to leave. No fridge in room (but did have ice bucket which made up for it).When I visit Vegas again I'll stay here again without hesitation. Perfect for me and my friends who wanted a good time and didn't want to spend thousands.	
Oct 11 2009 	About as Average as they come	We took a long Labor Day weekend and spent 5 nights starting September the 4th at the Planet Hollywood. We booked a (Bellagio) fountain view room through Allegiant Airlines in a package that included air and hotel for what I thought was a good rate. We arrived in Las Vegas at 6PM on Friday of a holiday weekend so rather than take a taxi; we went to CLS shuttle. (In the past I have used taxis to get to the hotels quicker, but they have the habit of taking Tropicana all the way to the strip and then inch there way to your hotel with the meter running rather than cut down Koval or one of the other streets that would get you there sooner). We were the first one on the shuttle going on that route so we had to wait about 20 minutes (rather than stand in the taxi line that long) for them to get a few more people, but that wasn’t too bad. Anyway the shuttle did utilize the back streets to get to our destination efficiently and I am quite pleased with CLS. By the way, the thing that I like about them is that on your return they pick you up when they say they will. not 20 or 30 minutes later like some other shuttle companies that I have experienced.The Planet Hollywood hotel itself is pretty average. The main dissatisfaction that I found was check-in. It took us 45 minutes of standing in line to get to check in. They do use a single queue line so that you don’t have to guess which line is moving the fastest, but you would think that adequate coverage could be provided for a check in on Friday night of a busy holiday weekend. This problem persisted all evening as I was back by this area around 11PM and still the line was just as long. There were several unstaffed positions at the reception counter. There is no excuse for this, it is not poor planning it is poor management. They know how many people are scheduled to check in and should provide accordingly. Our room, 2193, was down near the end of the hall and did indeed have a nice view of the Bellagio fountains. The hallway and the room itself were done in dark woods and dark colors and of course they scrimp on the lighting in the rooms so it is always dark. In keeping with the Hollywood theme, the room was done with artifacts of ‘Lost in Space’. The bathroom was large and had a separate shower and tub. There was no refrigerator and of course they want to charge you $13 a day for high speed internet. This is another gripe that I have with ‘classy’ hotels; they nickel-dime you for things that a Super 8 for $60 a night includes as standard. Maid service was very good as it seemed that they watched for us to leave in the morning and whether we were gone an hour or several hours our room was always serviced when we returned. Overall the room was quiet and comfortable and of course a big positive with PH is Location, right in the center of the action on the strip.The casino is average also, about the same variety of machines and table games and the ‘scalp’ rate seems to be standard. I would stay here again if I could get a good deal, but there are usually better deals to be had especially now that things are a little slower.	
