Oct 10 2009 	Great stay with great promotions	I booked my trip to Vegas and decided to stay at the Planet Hollywood Resort. Resort is a very loose term because it was more of a hotel with pools, casino and spa. The entire place was extremely clean. It was modern in the sense of decor and hip. The king size bed room that I had was very spacious. The bathroom had a large jacuzzi tub and plenty of space to two people to be in the bathroom at one time. The king size bed was very comfortable and the room was spacious. Each room had a different movie theme and I was lucky enough to celebrate my two year anniversary in the Chucky Room! The pool area had a lounge area with lounge chairs where you can lay out away from the pools. There are two pools, one on each side of the pool area. The pool area has lounge chairs and a few umbrellas to shade yourself from the hot Vegas sun. It can be a bit difficult to find a chair by the pool area but it's not impossible. The casino had a good amount of tables and plenty of slots. The best part of the stay was the promotion they were running. If your stay is a minimum of three nights, each night of your stay you have a coupon for a free full size bottle of booze. You have one coupon that is dated for each night so you can only use the coupon for that date. There's only one selection for each type of alcohol, ie: wine, vodka, whiskey etc. Overall it was a greaqt stay at a hotel centrally located on the strip (next to Paris and across the street from the Bellagio). I would definitely stay there again!	
