ravelled to the south rim of the Grand Canyon with the Grand Canyon Tour Company. Their driver is brilliant and the price was great. Unfortunatley there were people who could not speak a word of English on our trip who held the bus up by 40 mins so we did not return home till 10pm that night, after arriving at the miracle mile shop valet at 6.10am. The Grand Canyon was the highlight of the trip, it is amazing and I would recommend going to the South Rim even though it is a very long day!The strip itself, quite shocked that there seem to be very few bars outsie of the hotels. The nightlife seems to be clubs or hotel bars. The location of the hotel is fantastic, it is right in the middle of the strip, located near some of the best hotels on the strip (Bellagio, Caesars palace). For the price it was good, but if I went there again I would stay elsewhere.	
