Oct 8 2009 	Great Location on the Strip - Parking is difficult	My friend and I found the Planet Hollywood hotel to be a very nice hotel with a great location right in the middle of the Strip. You can easily walk to other hotels and attractions on the strip. The hotel room was very nice with a large bathroom (separate tub and shower) and also a good sized room. The staff was helpful but when we checked in there was over 50 people in line and it took the staff about 20 minutes to bring out extra staff to try and clear the line. It ended up taking us over 1 1/2 hours to check in. This situation was caused by the drop off of 2 bus loads of people all at once but the hotel did not appear to be ready for this large influx of people. It seemed like the hotel should have known that this group was coming and prepared better for their checkin. The staff was trying hard to work with each group but it was a long wait to check into a hotel. Also parking is quite complicated for this hotel. The parking structure is about a 1/2 mile from the hotel (very little signage to know where to go) so it is quite a walk if you want to get your car in and out. Also the entrance for the hotel is on the back side of the hotel with no easy entry from the street. If you are willing to pay for valet service then this would not be a problem. The hotel, mall and casino are well appointed and my friend and I had a very good time in the casino. There are quite a few restaurants in the hotel and they gave us discount coupons for the restaurants but we did not eat at them because I was not feeling too well so I can not comment on their quality. The staff tried very hard to accommodate us during our stay and they were all courteous and helpful. I would stay at this hotel again.	
