Oct 8 2009 	Our Best Vegas Trip Ever	My husband and I have been to Vegas twice before, and stayed in cheap hotels, but this trip was so much more fun and definately worth the extra expense. We arrived on a Wednesday morning, checked in early with no wait in line and received an upgrade on our room without having to ask. We were expecting a typical tacky, garish Vegas motif and were pleasantly surprised by the wonderful decor of the hotel and whimsical room details. Accomidations were spacious, comfortable and very quiet. Our carpet was stained badly and the lighting was much too dim. The bathroom was huge, but the tub was teeny tiny. There was a small, yet irritating daily &quot;resort charge&quot; for bottled water and a newspaper. There is no coffee maker in the room. Overall we were pleased with our room. The casino was one of our favorites on the strip. The dealers, servers, and staff were friendly, helpful and entertaining. The location is fantastic--just a short walk to my favorite attraction at the Bellagio fountains. We were able to visit everything on the strip (except the Stratosphere) on our 4 day vacation without paying for tranportation except to and from the airport. We wondered why there were no picures on the web of the swimming pools , but once we saw them we understood. If you like to swim and sun in a beautiful atmosphere, don't stay at PH. The pool area is pathetic. By far, the best food we had on our trip was the buffet at PH. I can't wait to go back! Totally worth the price and you can find great coupons very easily. The other restaurants were also great and the selection is outstanding.  Overall, we loved PH--definately a memorable trip.	
