Oct 8 2009 	There are better hotels in Vegas for the same price.	Just back from another great trip to Vegas. This time I stayed at the Planet Hollywood Hotel and to be honest, although the holiday was great, the hotel was just about average. My comments are about the hotel and Vegas in general.Hotel -The lobby is quite impressive looking and the casino floor is quite modern but the rooms are very dated and in serious need of attention. We had a room on the 21st floor overlooking a building site (soon to be the new Aria hotel). You could hear the building work from very early in the morning.The bedroom itself had everything you would need and the bathroom was large with plenty of towels etc but it just all looked very old and tired. 3 years ago I stayed in a Pyramid room at the Luxor for less money and the room was much better. Planet Hollywood attracts quite a young clientele and this becomes quite apparent during the day around the pool.The pool area opens at 9am each morning. There are 2 swimming pools. One opened at 9am and to get a lounger at this pool you really needed to be there ready and waiting at 9am. The other pool opened at 10am and this one included a VIP area.There was a large area in between both pools full of sun loungers and it never seemed very busy. We always had a choice of where to lie. It really only filled up on Saturday - but then all of Vegas fills up at the weekend.The poolside snack bar was excellent. Great food and very reasonable. A large plate of chopped fruit was only $3 and most hot sandwiches, wraps etc were about $10 including fries. A large bottle of water with ice was $4.50.Food -For breakfast we mainly used Starbucks or Earl of Sandwich on the casino floor. If we were having a late breakfast we would just use the poolside snack bar. There are also a few places for breakfast in the Miracle Mile shopping centre.We also found a very nice Italian restaurant at the Miracle Mile shops for dinner. It is directly opposite the theatre and fountain. The food was very good and quite reasonable priced. A Mexican restaurant beside it was also very good.Our best meal was at the Terrace Pointe Café in The Wynn Hotel. (I recommend the chicken risotto dish if it’s on the menu). My tip would be to book a table at this restaurant (request outside seating – it’s superb) and then head to the “Parasol Down” bar for pre-dinner drinks (located at the bottom of a curved escalator). You can request a table outside for drinks here as well although there may be a small waitlist. The outside seating area is great as there is a wall/water show every half hour. It only lasts a few minutes but with a glass of champagne and a relaxing atmosphere it is really a lovely experience.We also ate at Wolfgang Puck in the MGM. This place was very good. Staff very attentive and the atmosphere was buzzing.Top of the World restaurant at the top of the Stratosphere is also very good.We ate twice in the Grand Lux café in the Venetian and had great meals both times.Shops -The best thing about Planet Hollywood was the fact that it was attached to the Miracle Mile shops. This is a great shopping area without the high-end designer brands.The Fashion Show Mall opposite The Palazzo/Venetian is a great shopping centre with Macy’s, Bloomingdales, Abercrombie &amp; Fitch etc and the Grand Canal Shops in the Venetian are among the best for designer clothes.The shopping is excellent. I filled an extra case for the journey home.Location -The location of the hotel is good as it is just about the middle of the strip. However, due to the amount of road works around the hotel at present, the traffic is often at a standstill and taxi fares are criminal as a result. If I go back in the next year or two I would definitely stay further up the strip at the Mirage/Venetian end as this is where we spent the majority of our time.Taxi –A taxi from the airport was about $10 - $12.Attractions – A gondola ride at the Venetian is quite cheesy but a great laugh especially when the gondolier bursts into song.Nighttime trip by helicopter along the strip is great.The fountain show at the Bellagio will always grab your attention.If you decide to walk along the strip it may be better to walk on the Bellagio side of the road. We tried to walk on Planet Hollywood side and there are large groups of guys handing out cards for strip clubs/call girls and they can get quite annoying after a while. The other side of the road seemed to be quieter but I could be wrong. We normally got taxis to whatever hotel we had decided to spend an evening at. It was quicker and cooler. We stayed during the last week of Sept and the temperature peaked at 103FTo sum up – Las Vegas is a fantastic destination but I really couldn’t recommend the Planet Hollywood hotel unless you are on a hen/stag and it is within budget.	
