Oct 3 2009 	Loved the hotel HATE the Westgate timeshare corporation PLEASE READ!	We had a great time at the Planet Hollywood Hotel. We visited for my 40th birthday and I certainly had an unforgetable birthday -- however, not for the right reasons! Let me begin this story...We flew into Vegas on Tuesday, September 29th and sailed right throught airport, into a taxi and right to Planet Hollywood. Check in couldn't have been easier -- I stood in line for about 3 minutes, my room was ready and we began our vacation without a single bump in the road!Our room was exactly what we thought -- on the 38th floor -- spacious with a king size bed and AMAZING view of the Bellagio fountain! We had access to the Green Room which had ice cold bottled water and little snacks to enjoy! Seriously, what could go wrong?The next day, we set out to get tickets to shows and enjoy Las Vegas and all it has to offer! We noticed while walking through Planet Hollywood and the Miracle Mile Mall, we were approached numerous times by folks in RED shirts being offered free show tickets/meals/gaming. We dismissed them -- after all, we were busy doing our own thing...we didn' t have time for them!Sadly, we forgot this theory our 3rd day in Vegas. We were approached by a very savy young man with a gorgeous smile and amazingly white teeth! He offered us free buffets and dining vouchers and free show tickets to see Peep Show -- just a few minutes of our time. So, we did it :(Here's how it works...1st. The guest relations folks who work for Westgate corporation (not Planet Hollywood) offer you anything you want for free -- free gambling ($200 worth), free food, free show tickets or a combination of the above.2nd. You must agree to listen to the sales pitch -- 90minutes of your time. So, my husband and I had so far accomplished what we set out to do -- we felt we had 90 minutes to offer (who knows, maybe a timeshare would be of intereste to us...NOT)3rd. You must give the WEstgate folks $20 to ensure you show up for your sales pitch...you get your money back at the end of the pitch.4th. You show up for your sales pitch and this immediate feeling of doom comes over you.5th. 2 hours later, your sales pitch is over and when you say NO, they bring over a sales manager to as how you salesman treated you....here's where our story gets good...Our salesman name was Mark, and he was kind and understood when we said we were not interested in investing a timeshare with Westgate resorts. Mark said we had to speak with a sales manager who was &quot;just going to ask how he treated us and if we had any questions&quot; LIE!!!!! Of course, all sales managers were in a meeting that upheld our time there...I was getting seriously irritated at this point -- we were now at 2 hours into this 90minute talk and no sales manager was available. Finally, the sales managers emerged and KRISTA arrived at our table. She asked the typical questions, but when asked if we were interested in purchasing a time share, we said &quot;no&quot; and so she offered us a different deal. She offered us a $60,000 deal with just a mere $5000 down and then a 17.99%apr for the next 15 years. She placed this on the table and left. I looked at my husband and laughed. Explained to our salesperson, Mark, we didn't have $5000 to put down nor where we interested in purchasing a timeshare. After another 15minutes goes by, KRISTA finally returns. I explain we don't have $5000 to put down and she immeadiately interrupts me and tells me not to focus on the down payment. She then offers us a $10000 deal with a mere $2000 down, 0%financing for 15 months. I tell her &quot;we are not interested in purchasing a time share&quot;. She asks why? I tell her &quot;this is not something that will work for my family&quot; As I'm speaking, KRISTA continually interrupts me and NEVER lets me finsih my sentences. At this point, I am so incredibly pissed off I can't see straight. She asks again, why aren't we interested and then offers a $179/mos. price for the next 12 years. I laugh and say, &quot;it's not happening -- I&quot;m trying to cut back my hours at work , not pick up more -- I want to spend more time with my children and allowing them to partake in their activities and investing in this company will not allow that&quot;. Again, during my time of speaking, KRISTA was interrupting me. She again asked &quot;WHY wouldn't we invest, our reasons weren't valid and were ridiculous&quot;. I then said we like to vacation in upstate New York on Skaneateles Lake and they didn't have places there -- she said they did. I said &quot;no you don't -- it's a private lake, there are NO timeshares there&quot;. KRISTA said they did have property there, so I told her to show me. She then said &quot;if I show you, will you buy a timeshare?&quot; I said &quot;probably not&quot;. So she said, &quot;then I'm not going to show you&quot;. At this point, I was seeing red and wanted to table flip (like Theresa did in the HOusewives of New Jersey). My husband finally looked at KRISTA and said &quot;we are not buying, we don't have the money&quot;. KRISTA raised her hands up in the air, slammed them on the table, and said &quot;fine&quot; and started to push away. I looked at her and said &quot;are you serious?, you'll listen to him and take his answer, but you won't take mine?&quot; She looked me straight in the eyes and said &quot;you weren't being honest with me&quot;. I said, &quot;so you are calling me a liar?&quot; And she looked at me, said &quot;yes&quot; and walked away from the table. I reported her behaior to guest services and filled out a complaint form -- sadly, but not surprisingly, I haven't heard anything. I hope that this will prevent anyone else from making the same, terrible mistake. There is no possible way that the dinner vouchers/buffet vouchers will ever make up for the unprofessionalism that is evident in the Westgate timeshare spiel. And to top it all off, this all happened on my 40th birthday :(I spoke to the Planet Hollywood hotel manager, and he said he would pass along my complaint, but Planet Hollywood hotel is not affilitated with the Westgate resort folks. However, the Westgate folks are like cockroaches all over Planet Hollywood, so you explain to me how they are seperate entities? The new tower is even called Planet Hollywood Tower by Westgate...Just be wary and I highly recommend avoiding the Westgate roaches like the plague.	
