Sep 24 2009 	Nice Hotel Excellent Location	We stayed at the hotel for 4 nights in September whilst travelling around the West Coast. We loved the hotel, it was in a fantastic location in the middle of the strip. our room was on the 7th floor overlooking the pool and Paris hotel. The room was large with two double beds. The room had a large flat screen tv and had two arm chairs and a desk and chair. The room was modern but the armchairs did look a little old. The room was very clean. There was also a safe in the room, there was wifi but there was a charge for this. The bathroom was large and had two sinks, a bath, a seperate shower and a toilet., again the bathroom was clean. There was no line when we checked into the hotel so we did not have to wait. The parking was free for both self park and valet, although if you used valet there was about a 20 minute wait to get the car back. The pool at the hotel was nice and was never too busy. There was always plenty of sunbeds free. We ate at P F Chang China Bistro in the hotel. The food was really nice and it was really good value for money. It is worth making a reservation as we had to wait about 45 minutes for a table but it was well worth the wait.	
Sep 24 2009 	Married at Planet Hollywood!	My fiance (now husband) and I stayed at Planet Hollywood from August 14-18, as we had booked a wedding package &amp; reception at PH. The only negative I can say abut the hotel was the length of time it took to check-in. This was our 4th trip to Vegas in two years, and all our previous experiences with hotel check-in in the city was that the lines (when there were lines) pretty much zipped along. I'm not sure if it was because PH doesn't have as many check-in stations, or if there was just an extraordinary number of people trying to check-in at the same time, but we were definitely in line well over an hour. However, the stress I felt from the wedding went away as soon as I saw our room. We had booked the &quot;Father of the Bride&quot; package which included a two night stay in one of PH's panorama suites. I have never seen such an amazing hotel room in my entire life. The room had a 180 degree panoramic view of the strip, with the focus being the Bellagio founains. The suite itself consisted of a seperate standard size hotel room, and the suite, which included two bathrooms, a living room, dining room, bar area, huge bedroom, and bathroom. The decor was fantastic - so clean, sleek, and modern. The rooms themselves were immaculate. Because it is Planet Hollywood, all accomodations have a different memorabilia theme. Ours was Star Trek, and it was fun to see how the different props and costumes were displayed in the room. It was definitely tasteful. The suite was so large and spacious. I think it was bigger than the condo we live in back home! I never wanted to leave, and it was nice to see how the upper half lives!! Upon check-in room service came to our suite witha basket of cheese, crackers, fruit, and chocolates. Our wedding ceremony was held in the chapel at Planet Hollywood. The chapel was very simple, elegant, and beautiful, and was the perfect size for our 20 guests. As part of the package we had a violonist who performed 3 songs of our choosing. The reception was held in our suite, and there was more than enough room and seating for everyone to eat and dance. The flowers, music, and cake were all customized for us, and the food that was brought up was out of this world, and that was also customized. The bar essentials were also included. The wedding planners and photographers really went above and beyond to make our day special, and the concierge staff was always so helpful. We would call room service and they would be at our door in no more than 5 minutes no matter how silly the request may have seemed. The next morning they brought us breakfast in bed. I've heard all of the stereotypes regarding Vegas weddings, and the event we had at Planet Hollywood really put all of them to bed. We had a beautiful day, and if anyone is looking for a location in Vegas to have their wedding that doesn't involve Elvis or a drive-thru, I would recommend Planet Hollywood in an instant. It was a memorable day for us and our guests.Aside from the wedding, Planet Hollywood is one of my favorite casinos on the Strip. It is very hip and trendy, and there are a lot of younger people there, so we didn't feel out of place like we do at some casinos. There are wonderful dining options like Koi and PF Chang's - while we were there my husband almost walked right into Tom Cruise and Katie Holmes as they were leaving PF Chang's, and he saw Holly Madison walking her dog through the casino! On the day we checked in there was a movie premiere, and the red carpet was rolled out. Very neat to see! The casino has an open floorplan, isn't smokey, is well lit, and just has a good vibe and energy to it. I'd definitely love to stay there again, and even if I don't, I will be sure to hit the slots there on my next trip back to Vegas!	
