Sep 11 2009 	Great Hotel	Stayed at Planet Hollywood for 10 nights from 30th Aug-9th Sept with my husband and had a great time. We were checked in within 5 mins and upon arrival we requested an upgrade and were given a Fountain View Room (2457) and also requested a Fridge for medication purposes which we were given no problem at no extra charge. Maid service was daily, cleaning bathroom and getting fresh towels etc. Only gripe with the cleaning was the corridors, the floors were rather grubby and hadn't been hoovered the whole time we were there which was a shame as I found rest of hotel rather clean.Our room had two queen size beds which were super comfy and fresh bed linen twice in the ten nights. Rooms were rather dark but that's what lamps are for and there were two lamps and one main light so it never caused us a problem.Bathroom was great, clean and spacious with a fab bath tub and nice marble vanity area and walk in shower which was also good. Hairdryer was also supplied.There are 2 swimming pools one of which didn't open until 10.00am which suited us and we never had any problems getting beds and pool area was kept clean with cleaners regularly coming round sweeping up and removing rubbish.This is a lively hotel and definately geared towards the younger age group which to me is a good thing as not everyone that goes to Vegas is over 50. Music around the pool was good and not too loud as I have read in other reviews albeit there is a DJ at the weekends which I must admit was rather loud.We ate in the Spice Market Buffet and Planet Daillies for Breakfast and both were really great. PF Changs Chinese within the hotel is fab and Earl of Sandwich is superb. Casino is well air conditioned and not smokey in the slightest and yes there are women dancing on tables but did not find this offensive in anyway and half the time didn't even notice they were there. Timeshare people were a pain but we just kept saying no thanks and walking on and it was fine.Overall this was a great hotel is superb location right in the centre of the srip with a bus stop right on the doorstep where you can catch the Deuce Bus which takes you up and down the strip as often as you like if you buy a daily ticket.Bellagio Fountains were absolutely stunning and the Volcano at the Mirage was spectacular and our Gondola Ride at the Venetian was fab.Tip: Avoid Labor Day Weekend, the place was jam packed, inside and out!	
