Sep 3 2009 	Great location so-so hotel	We stayed in Planet Hollywood on our recent trip to Las Vegas. We took advantage of their US$59 per night promo. We even got free bottles of champagne. The only catch was that we paid before we stayed, which was okay. What we loved most about the hotel was the location. It was right on the Strip so we were able to walk from there to either Encore up north or Luxor down south. We stayed at an accessible room because it was the only nonsmoking room available at that time. It was a good place to sleep at the end of the day but it seemed tired, which we didn't expect when we checked in because the lobby was hip and modern, almost like a W hotel. The room was clean though.The bathroom was huge but whenever either of us took a shower, the part of the bathroom which should be dry would be flooded. We were warned that this would happen and they said this is normal, but I think hotel management should consider installing sliding doors instead of shower curtains so areas that should be dry will stay dry.We also found the food at Spice Market Buffet mediocre. We didn't feel bad about it though because we ate there for free. (We got a voucher from listening to a two-hour talk about Westwood timeshare.) If you really have to eat on-site, Planet Dailies is a good choice. We ate there twice and we loved what we got both times. Service there is satisfactory too. There are other dining options at the hotel but we weren't able to try them.Avid shoppers should consider staying at Planet Hollywood because the Miracle Mile shops are located here. You can access the shops via the casino so you can avoid the sun and the heat.Overall, Planet Hollywood is good but could be better.	
