have been nice to see.3- There are constantly people harassing you to come check out their new condo property and they keep enticing you with bogus claims of free dinners, shows, casino $. Smile once and then walk out through the shopping mall to avoid them.4- The comp dollars are a joke its nearly impossible to rack up anything unless you waste your time on slots.To conclude, I would certainly go back to PH as it was the hippest casino that has a great location, affordable pricing, and size that is not large enough to get lost but big enough to party hard!	
Aug 10 2009 	Great Location Good Food Decent Room	My husband and I just returned from a weekend at Planet Hollywood. We got a great rate through a Starwood connection or we probably would not have chosen this hotel. That said, I was completely satisfied with several aspects of Planet Hollywood. The check-in line was long but when we finally got to the desk, the agent was professional and helpful. He found us large room with a great view of the Bellagio fountains. He also passed along the tip that you can get a $10 discount on the fitness center if you provide your Starwood Preferred number upon check in. The fitness center is usually $25, but it does include all-day access to the whirlpool, sauna and steam room in the spa. The spa isn't very deluxe, however. The room was fine; large, with a comfy bed, good pillows and linens. The TV doesn't face the bed, which is strange, but who watches TV in Las Vegas anyway? The room is slightly worn in general but clean enough that the frayed carpet didn't gross us out. The bathroom was huge with a nice jacuzzi tub and separate shower stall, two separate sink/vanities and a WC with door. The towels are horrible - thin, worn, faded purple things. But overall, we were very comfortable.We had two meals in the hotel; at Yolos Mexican Grill and Planet Dailies coffee shop. Both were far better than expected with excellent, friendly service and very good food. Tip: If you're at the Bellgio and the line for the cafe is too long, try Planet Dailies right across the street. I thought the food was better there.The guests and much of the staff at the hotel are very young. This was fine for us, but people who don't like a club-like environment with loud dance/pop/rock music playing all the time shouldn't stay here.The attached Miracle Mile Mall has the usual mall assortment of shops. The property was formerly the Alladin and midway through the mall the decor reverts to Alladin style, Arabian Nights motif, which is kind of weird. But whatever; it's Las Vegas.For young people, or for anyone who gets a really good rate, Planet Hollywood is a good Las Vegas hotel in a great location.	
