ce to their club Prive on the casino level if we arrived before 11pm. As Jermaine Dupri was DJing that night we decided to go. Getting into the club was a little difficult as you have to push yourself to the front of the lines to get the door employees' attention, but inside the service was good, JD was good that night and overall it was a very fun scene.	
Jul 24 2009 	PH is AWSOME!	My wife and I made our first trip to PH from July 19-23. We arrived to PH on time and were greeted very kindlu and directed to the check-in counter. Check-in was very fast and easy. We were given many options of rooms they had available and opted for a mountain view (room 3464). We got up to the room and we were both pleasantly surpeised with how nice the room was for the price that we paid. The rooms are themed after movies and we got &quot;The Finstones&quot; room. The Casino is very trendy and hip towards the 21-35 year old demographic. The casino level itself is very clean along with the washrooms (cleanest on that side of the strip). The Miracle Mile shops are trendy and reasonably priced with some big name stores.We decided to checkout the Steve Wyrick magic show which is hels at the Steve Wyric Theatre in PH. We heard it is one of the best in Vegas. We were not dissappointed. Don't buy your show tickets at the hotels. There is a &quot;discount ticket&quot; place along the strip at the enterance to O'Shea's. They sell tickets to all Vegas shows for half off, or more.We only ate at PH twice as we found we were always somewhere else when we were hungry. We ate at &quot;Earl of Sandwhich&quot; it was good and reasonably priced and we ate at Planet Dailies which was not tasty and a little over priced.The pool area is not the greatest. There are 2 pools located on the 6th floor. You better get there really early to get a seat by the pool. If you don't you will be sitting quite far away as the poolside seating area is small. The slot play at PH is VERY tight. the table dealers aren't the nicest eaither. We found ourselves gambling at the Flamingo. Thier BJ tables were always paying out.The location of PH is great, the value is great, the atmosphere is great, the cleanliness is great and the employees are kind. We WILL stay here again.	
