Jul 22 2009 	We prefer PH	We booked this hotel for a friend's birthday and traveled with my husband and three other couples. We booked PH because of the central location on the strip and promo of one free bottle of alcohol per day. Check in was painless. We got there about 3:30pm on Thursday afternoon and maybe waited 5 minutes. I was really expecting our free bottle of alcohol to be very small. However I was pleasantly surprised when I went to claim it. There were several selections and the alcohol bottles were 750ml each. You could chose between Skyy vodka, Bacardi light rum, Sauza tequila, and a few different bottles of wine or champagne. We stuck with the Bacardi and Skyy. The juices in the lobby store were almost a dollar more than at Walgreens, but the convenience far outweighed the price for us. We wanted to at least make a few drinks before venturing out on the strip. Since we were there with several other couples we each got something different to share. We upgraded to a Resort room which is a bit bigger than the standard room and we had a view of the strip. We figured our room would be the central party room for our group. The only complaint I have about the room is the shower. However I don't think I have stayed at any hotel on the strip where the shower was great. I was also pleasantly surprised at the lack of noise. We have stayed at PH a few times in the past and have had to endure the sound of the other doors around us slamming shut at all hours of the night. This time however I did not hear one door. Not sure if it was because of the bigger room or the fact that there weren't very many people around us. Either way I was quite happy. I was originally going to complain about the fact that you now have to pay 5.99 for two bottles of water and the morning paper every day but I did find this convenient. We usually end up walking down the strip to Walgreens a few times during our trip to get water. This saved us the trip. Also it was nice because it was 113 two of the days we were there and 108 the other two days so we tried to stay off the strip as much as possible. And with the free alcohol that we took advantage of, I could not complain about paying 2.50 each for water. We took advantage of the pool one of the days. We were able to get chairs around the pool this time with an umbrella. I guess this was because the sun was not out all day. That was fine with us. We had a great time. The cocktail waitress was really nice and attentive. No complaints about the pool either. The casino itself is okay. I don't think I was offered a drink by any of the cocktail waitresses when playing the slots. My husband had better luck getting drinks at the tables. Again this is the same with the other casinos I have visited so I don't know if I can totally fault PH for this. We ate at Earl of Sandwich one time, which was very good, and Planet Dailies one time which was not so good. However it was almost 5 am so again I can't really complain about the food. No place is that great at 5am. in my opinion. If they still have the free alcohol deal at PH the next time we go, I will stay there without a doubt.	
