Jul 21 2009 	Wanna get robbed? Stay here...	If you expect to be ROBBED and treated like dirt by the hotel staff then this is the place for you. Long story...but I encourage you to read this review and take my advice...DO NOT STAY AT PLANET HOLLYWOOD!On the surface this hotel/casino looks great and the rooms are pretty nice. Let me start by saying my friends and I have stayed at this hotel since 2005 when it was the Aladdin and we used to rave about how great this hotel was...after it changed to PH I have a completely different outlook and will NEVER stay again, or recommend this hotel. In 2008 we stayed on the 12th floor in a room right off of the elevators (can't remember the exact number now). On the second day we were there our room was robbed of 3 purses, WHILE WE WERE SLEEPING. We were awakened by a phone call from hotel security informing us that a housekeeper found our purses in one of the stairwells. We went to security and collected what was left of our belongings and filed a report. We were very shaken and a loss prevention woman, Michelle something or other came up to the room and took photos of our room like that was going to answer questions. She failed to take any photos of the broken door that we unknowingly and according to her &quot;carelessly left ajar for someone to enter.&quot; She also mentioned that, &quot;This happens frequently.&quot; Random people off the street are always coming to the 12th floor, and finding open doors to steal from PH guests. Odd the chances that someone got lucky enough to search a cameraed hotel of almost 40 floors and over 2600 rooms and actually steal 4 purses. GREAT SECURITY ASSURANCE don't you think? Oh and there just so happened to be no security cameras in the hotel hallways nor the stairwells. However, lucky for us security could let us know that our door had been left ajar for a 3 hour time period which was the window of opportunity. (That random thief sure got lucky choosing PH and our 12th floor to rob from in that small time frame). Odd how they can tell me that but don't have cameras and couldn't knock on our door to let us know that it was left open. The customer service was horrible. They did nothing to assure us we were safe nor did they offer us anything for our inconvenience. We had to follow up in 5 to 7 business days to find out if anything came up. (Of course nothing did and we have yet to get reimbursed for our stolen items.) After the incident we were being a lot more careful throughout the rest of our stay and in one instance realized the door was not closing properly behind us so we called security to report the problem and maintenance to take a look at it and fix it. No one ever came to help us. We were very disappointed but figured maybe this was an isolated incident and because of our liking for the hotel/casino in past years we stayed their again...	
