Jul 14 2009 	Very nice hotel but bring $$$	We stayed at Planet Hollywood July 1-8 and had no problem at all with check-in. I have read that there are long lines but we did not encounter them. There was a bit of a wait at checkout but using the Express Checkout box they have will avoid this. The room we had was in the theme of the Lost In Space movie with a few items used in the movie plus 2 movie posters. Sorry I forgot to take pictures of them. I requested a high floor overlooking the strip and got what I think was very good. There was a little bit of a view of the roof but you could see other hotels and the mountains (see photo). We were placed on the 14th floor which was a very quiet floor and we were away from the elevators. The music they play throughout the hotel and elevators is great. We were traveling with 2 teenage girls and they agreed. Much better music selection here than at the Hard Rock Hotel.A major flaw for me to this hotel was they don't provide coffeemakers and if you are a coffee drinker, you can spend a substantial amount at Starbucks, which is in every hotel, or eating at one of the restaurants. We tried the Spice Market buffet for lunch and was very pleased with it. Food from around the world was here so you have a good selection. Be sure to use your coupon if you have one or get a coupon book in the Miracle Mile mall for other discounts. Beer was a ripoff in the casino, $7 so I didn't dare get a mixed drink. You can buy a six-pack down the street in the novelty shops for a dollar more. The location was very good, walking distance to a lot of the other hotels and shops. The mall itself is very nice with a lot of different stores, high end and low end. Yolo's Mexican restaurant in the casino has very good food. Try the lunch special. The chambermaid was very pleasant and accommodating. The pool was well attended but if you want a seat next to the pool, get there by 11am. The large center sitting area is very nice and they have a hot food stand there also.I expected a little more in the way of fireworks since we were there for the 4th of July but not a lot were set off. That same day, Steve Wyrick was doing a stunt outside the hotel and thousands of people were on the street watching. The least the hotel could have done was show what was happening on their huge marquis but nada. We never even knew the stunt was over until the police said it was done and we can now leave. A waste of time and inconvenience for the drivers since the strip was shut down for almost an hour.Overall it was a good experience but you need to bring lots of cash, especially if you're going to gamble or party. Don't bother renting a car if you don't plan on going out of the city. The bus will get you up and down the main part of Las Vegas Blvd. and into Fremont St. for $7 for 24 hours.	
