Jun 4 2009 	Planet Hollywood-Out of this world?	We just returned from a 3 night stay at Planet Hollywood. I know the reviews on this site have been mixed, but we got a good rate and since it is in such a good location on the Strip decided to try it.(We had stayed there when it was the Aladdin). The best thing about the room was the great bathroom! It was very large, had a separate large tub, shower, and room for toilet as well as a big vanity top. The bed was very comfortable, the room very clean, and although the window was on the small size, we had a nice view of the pool and partial view of the strip. We were near the elevator but heard no noise at all. There was no &quot;do not disturb &quot; sign so I made my own and hung it on the doorknob and when the maid came by she did put a printed one in the key opening. (I do think it's odd that those signs are not in each room) I asked for an extra 45 min. extension on checkout, and was cheerfully given it. We ate several times at the Planet Dailies-portions are quite large and we split our breakfast order and had plenty for the 2 of us. Internet service available in room but for $13.99-I think that should be free. Having the Miracle Mile Mall attached is a big plus. There are 2 ABC stores there where you can find reasonable prices for misc. items, and a Coffee Bean store with free WIFI (very slow, but free) It was also nice to be able to shop without going out in the heat. The Duece Bus stop is right in front of the hotel and that was convenient for going up and down the Strip.I wasn't that impressed with the Casino-maybe I'm too old to appreciate the Pleasure Pit.All in all, maybe not out of this world, but certainly good value for the money.	
Jun 3 2009 	Loved Stay at PH but one bad flaw.........	We stayed at PH over Memorial Day weekend (5/23 - 5/26) and for the most part enjoyed our stay. The room was clean and we had enough room to move around (it was 4 of us, 3 girls, 1 guy. Thank goodness for the large bathroom :)). Room also looked just like the pictures. Arrived at 11:30 that morning and was immediately checked in. Staff was very friendly. Planet Dailies had good food for reasonable prices. Location of hotel is the best as it is in the middle of the strip. you just walk out of the hotel onto the strip and decide if you want to go to the left or right :) Also loved the Miracle Mile Shops. It was nice to be able to walk around and pick up anything that you may have forgotten. The casino was nice as well but didnt spend a lot of time in it. Only went to the pool once, PH should think about upgrading the pool area since you can equate it to getting in your pool in your backyard. My only complaint about PH is the night club Prive. We tried to go that Sunday night and had a terrible experience. After standing in line for over an hour (mind you we were there before they even started letting people in so we were right up front) to get into a so NOT crowded club, one of the host was trying to get some of his friends in and trying to get them to jump the line. Make a long story short, he walked up to us and said &quot;move or be moved&quot;, some words were exchanged, he instructed his clients to, and I quote, &quot;just knock them over&quot;and then it really turned into a big scene. It was a big mess and the people working at Prive are ignorant and disrespectful. There were a lot of witnesses to the incident as there were more people waiting in line than were actually in the club and many of them walked off because they couldnt believe what had just happened and because they had been standing in line waiting for over an hour as well. They were actually picking and choosing who they were going to let in the club and if you didnt look a certain way, well you were not getting in. Its is really sad to witness this type of discrimination in 2009, but what can you say. It is their club and they can let in who they would like. My suggestion for people of color, older couples, foreigners (unless asian), people not willing to pay the bouncers $100 plus to get pass the rope (and still have to pay to get in once you get up the escalator), and for people who dont like to go out naked reading this, just go to another club and dont waiste your time at Prive. Security at PH was very helpful and after the incident provided us with the corporate number and address to call and lodge a complaint as the employees of Prive are not employed by PH. Will something be done, probably not, but we will NEVER EVER attempt to go to Prive again. But PH may want to be careful because if instances like this continue, future guests may associate Prive with PH and decide not to stay at PH ever again.	
