May 17 2009 	Great place for 20 somethings to have an unforgettable weekend!	So my friends and I (8 of us all together) decided to take a trip to Vegas from LA. It was gonna be our first road trip! I've been to vegas before, so I looked at different hotels. We got the BEST deal at PH! We ordered their KRAVE package off of their website! It included 2 Mandara Spa passes, 2 club Krave passes, and a 2 bed hotel room for only 126 bucks a night, so we got two rooms!We got to the hotel and there was free valet. It was a friday when we arrived, and there was a huge line for valet, but hey instructed us to just leave our car in the line and they would take care of it. Valet and self parking is free. awesome!The check in girl could not have been more nice! She gave us adjoining rooms and also offered a view of the bellagio hotel, but the rooms weren't adjoining so we opted out of the view rooms. We were also there to see Mel B in Peepshow, and she gave us some passes to save 20 bucks on VIP tickets to the show! Score!As it says in the other reviews the rooms are really cool! We got the Michelle Phiffer and Daryl Hannah rooms! Its fun to see catwoman in your bathroom! :) there were really nice flat screen TVs, a little sit down area, and also a desk. The bathrooms are really cool! A massive tub, a huge area to &quot;put our faces&quot; on, and tons of toiletries.We called them to bring up two refridgerators for our drinks and left the room. When we came back to our rooms they were already set up and plugged in. I love that!The hotel is right in the epicenter of EVERYTHING! Perfect location! Also it's attached to the Miracle Mile shops, so there are a ton of places to shop, and a lot of great restaurant and drink places right in your hotel!We used the club passes on saturday night, and with cover being $20 bucks a pop, we saved $80 bucks right there!We didn't really have time to use the spa passes, which are normally $20 each, too, but that's because we took a tour of it and it was kind of lame. The spa is semi-small, and the fitness center is relatively semi-small, too. We ended up going to the spa at Ceasars Palace, which is $45 bucks each but SOOO worth it, and using the PH spa passes just to spruce up during mid day and grab some fruit and drinks from the lounge.The pool was really great! It's a nice massive pool with a hot tub right next to it! Plenty of room to sun bathe, and not as crowded as the pools at caesars palace or rio, so it is really enjoyable!All in all it was a really great hotel that accommodated all of our needs! In the future I would just self park your car, as the wait for our car to be brought back to us was about 1/2 hour. The self parking spots are really not far away at all, and as everyone is able bodied in your group that's probably a better bet time wise. I don't think there was internet in the room, which kind of sucks, but whatever, who needs it when you're with your friends and in the center of the strip!	
May 15 2009 	Planet Hollywood Vegas...Smaller than others but chic and sexy!	My boyfriend and I stayed at the Planet Hollywood Las Vegas from May 10-14 2009. The hotel first caught my attention in an episode of PRISON BREAK last season. This former restuarant (are there any still open?) has definitely revamped its look from their cheesy red and blue shooting star logo to a much modern purple &quot;ph&quot; . Check-in was quick and easy for us because we didn't arrive until almost 10pm. By the ways, if you decide to take the taxi from the airport-MAKE SURE TO TELL THE DRIVER NOT TO TAKE THE FREEWAY to the strip. It is a complete rip-off as the freeway route will cost you almost $30. As we learned later, the shuttles usually take Paradise Road, which I believe runs parallel to the strip. Anyhow, the downside of taking a shuttle when you arrive is that it may take you an hour to get to your hotel because of all the stops. So take your pick.The room: The hotel room itself was very clean and spacious. There was celebrity memorabilia in our room so I am guessing that all rooms have that as well. The sheets are soft and white. There is a large flatscreen TV in the room with high-def channels. This was good for the down times when we needed to recharge from all the heat and walking around. There was no mini-bar or fridge in our room (resort suite), but that was fine by us because we are &quot;thrift&quot; anyways. Before leaving, I read the reviews that mentioned consistently how the room tends to be on the dark side. My boyfriend noted this as well. although I thought the lighting was fine myself. I guess this depends on your preference. They did have a moth screen that filtered out more sunlight than a typical hotel room. This didn't bother us either since the view wasn't so hot anyhow. A nice surprise was that they supplied us with a brand new edition of OKAY! magazine in the room. There was no coffeemaker in our room, just a ice bucket with tongs and some glasses. I don't iron my cloths usually on vacation, but there is one in the room. The bathroom: Pretty spacious for two people as well. There is a large granite counter. The bathroom comes with a hairdryer, shampoo, massage soap (yes!) shower cap (yes!), conditioner, shower gel, and lotion and conditioner. The sizes were generous and the maids brought extra ones once we ran out. There was also 4 bottles of axe body spray samples that the boyfriend happily brought back with him. There is a stand up shower and a tub as well. I liked that there was bathmat so I could step out of the shower on to dry my feet instead of wasting a towel for this. My only complaint about this room was the amount of time it took for the shower to warm up. On average, it took at least 5-6 minutes in the morning. Once it warmed up, it never gets too hot either. Kind of a waste if you think about all the water wasted in warming up the shower, but wastefulness seems to be the running theme in Vegas in general anyhow. My boyfriend had to take a cold shower one night because I think they must have past their hot water quota for the day. Amenities-wise, we took advantage of the fitness room and the pool. Loved the pool!! It had a very hip vibe to it with club music playing and enough eye candy for some good people-watching. The fitness room was decent. There is tons of cardio and weight-lifting machines. There is complimentary water (via water dispenser) and fruit (apples and oranges). Be sure to take some of the fruit because they are a rip-off everywhere else. The downside? It is $25US/day! Be sure to use the 2 for 1 coupon that you get when you check-in. Check-out was easy. We took the express check-out via the television in the room. Since our plane didn't leave until 7pm that evening, the hotel had the service where we were able to store our luggage until we left for the airport. This was free (but we tipped the bellboy of course). One last thing, I would highly highly highly recommend the show &quot;Mesmerized&quot; with Marc Savage. Its a hypnosis show with audience members participating. We both found it to be very funny and entertaining since you can tell that it is not entirely scripted nor does it strive to be politically correct. GO SEE IT!!!! We also saw Tony N' Tina's Wedding. It was good also, but definitely not as good as Mesmerized. It is definitely more slapstick and the traditional in its comedy routine.	
May 13 2009 	GREAT POSITION- GREAT HOTEL	It all read up fine but we didn't know it! From reception to every aspect the staff were friendly and helpful. The room- great..bed like sleeping on a cloud, all very clean and pleasant to be in for 5days. The 25th floor view over Bellargio with the nightly watershow was magnificent. A big bonus definately the Mile of shops. and we found great eating spots (and some of the clothing shops had great deals) The biggest plus is Planet's position it is perfect!!! You can walk along the strip- catch a bus..all at your fingertips. We are going back again next year and will stay there for sure. Highly recommend.,	
May 13 2009	Best Place in the World!	Chose the hotel due to its location - being our 4th time in Vegas we knew being by Paris, Bellagio, Caesars and a slow stroll from NYNY and MGM was well appointed. I think we paid £50/$70 a night which was superb bearing in mind 18 months ago we'd paid £180/$240 a night for a fountatin view at Belagio (where we got married!/engaged at MGM approx 10 yrs ago - so from this you can tell this place means a lot to us!). The result being we got upgraded to a strip view room of the strip and most importantly of the Belagio fountains - which are simply amazing.Having done Bellagio and Wynn last time I didnt expect to be as blown away as we were! Seriously this place may not be 5* but its a 4*+++++ in my humble opinion. We stayed in T.I. for out final 3 nights which is also a 4* and if you are toying between these 2 hotels then trust us = its a no brainer - book Planet Hollywood right now! Room was very big, a lot of reviews mention rooms being dark and yes they are a bit but when we got back to the room we wanted to crash out so did we want a bright room? Erm no! So not a problem - unless obviously you want to spend hours in the room which we didnt! Room itself - gorgeous - our theme room was Bette Midler/Burt Reynolds film which was a shame but hey it was different - i cant say ive stayed in a room before where there was film memorabilia there! Room itself was fantastically well appointed as it was 1st room on 30th floor right by the lifts. We counted 30 steps from room to casino! Beat that! Think it was 3067? Stayed there sunday 3rd may for 6 nights. Bathroom huge with separare lockable toilet, walk in shower and separate bath tub. Also a huuuuge window ledge big enough to sit on and watch the bellagio founatins! Huge plasma - i guess 42 inch and one of the most comfortable beds we've ever stayed in. People spoke of thin walls but we didnt hear any neighbouring rooms during whole stay. Loved the restaurants in there = P F Chang - gorgeous - go 4 their lunch bowls for $8 each or Im sure an eve meal would be amazin too. Earl of sandwich do these ham / cheese / egg b/fast rolls for about $4 which are the perfect motivator to get out of bed for! Buffet is always voted best in vegas - gotta be honest here - the best is Wynn but its also more expensive. Planet Dailies blew us away food quality-wise as we were only using it to supplement the cost of seeing the Mel B/Kelly Monaco Peepshow (which i must add was excellent-VIP seats were perfect)- we had duck and a chicken pasta which were gorgeous. 1st night we ate in Yolos Mexican - food was incredible and the cocktails were world class - only slight criticism is that portions were smaller than we expected - to be fair though we expected that whole tex-mex thing but this place is actually at a higher standard than that so we agreed that was why they werent overdoing the portions. Casino very cool - maze-like and we were always lost but very cool.All in all Ive recommended this hotel to about 20 people already and we only got back today - in fact if any planet hollywood representative reading this fancies flying us back out there we'd be well up for it!! Missed Holly from Playboy Mansion and Ashanti who were by the pool when we went shopping at the Fashion Show Mall for the day and also missed Diddy filming outside the hotel on our last day so when heard we were gutted!! All in all - what a hotel - what a location! And when City Centre opens later this year the location is going to be EVEN better - can't wait to get back to Vegas and Plant Hollywood will be top of the list when we do!!	
May 13 2009 	Great Stay	We stayed at the Planet Hollywood for four nights. The Planet Hollywood is in a perfect location on the Vegas Strip. Our room was very large. The bathroom was huge. There was a large LCD TV in the room, two big windows, and the most comfortable beds. Everything was clean, well stocked and in good working order. The only issue we faced was with a toilette that got plugged, but they were to our room in 10 minutes to fix it.	
May 13 2009 	Perfect Room Friendly Casino	We got a great deal through Allegiance Air on this hotel - roundtrip airfare for two plus three nights in a Hollywood Hip room for $640 total. The rooms themselves are on the small side, but the bathroom are huge. The only other place where I've had a bathroom that large was at Caesars Palace in an upgraded Tower Room for at least twice the price. I realize PH dolled up their smaller rooms and called them &quot;Hollywood Hip&quot; to slap a premium price on them (the cheaper rooms are actually larger), but I don't spend much time in the room so I don't care. The casino's signage is lacking, but the friendly staff and dealers more than make up for it. Although I prefer other casinos' poker rooms, PH's is decent. The pools are clean and there were ample chairs even on Saturday morning. The $3 Bud Light Lime special at the pool was great. The restaurants in the Casino were all quality. Yolo's is the best for a moderately priced lunch or dinner. The Strip is a fantastic steakhouse with food comparable to The Prime's and less pretentious service - no view of the fountains though. The location of PH is great, central to all the major casinos. My only complaint is that they still charge $12.95/day for internet.	
May 12 2009 	Excellent location on The Strip	Overall this is a great hotel, especially when you compare it to others on the strip. The location is excellent, close to both the south and north ends. Stay away from the Spice Market Buffet -- gross!! Never again!! Planet Dailies was good food. The pool was alright, nothing exciting and it closed at 7pm (I thought this was way too early). I liked the atmosphere of this hotel. Lots to see and do. Watch out for the coupon books offering 2 for 1 drinks. One drink cost $9 (how is this a deal??). Would stay here again.	
